            "commit": "078a099d26ef7f5d26131c0e18615855a39f341d",
            "subject": "LU-9841 lov: do not split IO for single striped file"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-08-09 18:30:02.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-08-28 06:25:06.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9410 ldiskfs: no check mb bitmap if flex_bg enabled",
        "message": "LU-9410 ldiskfs: no check mb bitmap if flex_bg enabled\n\nWhen initializes (reformat) the filesystem, the number of\nfree blocks in the group descriptor is calculated via the\next2fs_reserve_super_and_bgd() (e2fsprogs). As commented\nin such function: \"This is not necessarily the case when\nthe flex_bg feature is enabled, so callers should take care!\".\n\nSo it is normal that we may find the block group descriptor\nthat has LDISKFS_BG_BLOCK_UNINIT flag but with 0 free blocks.\nThe ldiskfs_mb_check_ondisk_bitmap() should NOT report error\nfor such block group, instead, skip the check directly.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iba0fb2bf0632a6e54222472bc724a8ea0478e9ae\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/28566\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
